# Smart Posts Project Rules

- Keep feature code in `lib/smartposts/` with `UI/`, `bloc/`, and `models/`.
- Keep shared strings, colors, dimensions, durations, and asset paths outside the feature in `lib/common/`.
- Put reusable, feature-independent widgets in `lib/common_widgets/`.
- Never hardcode user-facing strings, colors, asset paths, or design dimensions in UI files.
- Use local assets only. Do not depend on remote images or backend/API calls.
- Use Flutter Bloc with separate `*_bloc.dart`, `*_event.dart`, and `*_state.dart` files.
- Register handlers with `on<Event>` and update state only with `emit`.
- Keep business state, timers, and transitions out of widgets.
- Use immutable models and states with `Equatable`.
- Add comments only for business logic, non-obvious interaction decisions, and important constraints.
- Follow SOLID principles where they improve separation, testability, and reuse; avoid unnecessary abstraction.
- Match the supplied Figma design at its 375x812 reference size, while preventing overflow on nearby mobile sizes.
- Reuse exported Figma assets exactly and verify image crop, spacing, typography, opacity, and layering.
- Run formatting, `flutter analyze`, and `flutter test` after substantive changes.
